An investigation in under way after a man's body was found on the shoreline of the River Clyde in Greenock.
Police were called to the scene, next to the Inverclyde town's Battery Park, at 11:06. Fire crews also attended.
A police spokeswoman said inquiries were under way to establish the man's identity and a post mortem examination would be carried out in due course to establish how he died.
BBC Scotland understands the death is not believed to be suspicious.
